topic.body:
Every user already has a private key so I was wondering if it is possible to create a site where every one can sign without having a certification authority (e.g. zeroid.bit).

In particular, I've been following the tutorial at http://127.0.0.1:43110/Blog.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Post:99:ZeroChat+tutorial trying to set `data/users/content.json` to the following:
```
{
 "files": {},
 "ignore": ".*",
 "inner_path": "data/users/content.json",
 "modified": 0.0,
 "signs": {},
 "user_contents": {
  "cert_signers": {},
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 10000
   }
  },
  "permissions": {}
 }
}
```

At the moment I'm having other issues with the site, but **should such an approach eventually work** or do I need a CA?
